extends ETReceiver<E>
    Receives chronologically ordered data from a ETChronologicCollection.

    If you want to iterate the data from the collection again you will have to call the reset method before requesting a new item.

    A ETChronologicCollection is used to make sure, that events are sorted beforehand, to reduce computation effort while receiving events.
